The reason is that the Warsaw Stock Exchange is in the hands of the state.
99 percent of the shares are in the hands of the Polish state, which within a few months wants to sell 60 percent of the shares.
The Czech economic newspaper E15 that the offer of the Poles has been the highest among those offered by those interested in the Prague Stock Exchange.
